rComments: Very nice and respected prof. Tries his best not to talk too much during class he knows he always talks for too long since he loves what he's doing, which is so interesting to see. Tons of material to cover this class, need to understand lots about eco. crisis, gentrification, and bunch of history related stuff since cities are built in the past.

As a science and humanities student taking this class to fulfill my social science credit, I highly enjoyed this course. It was very interesting and Dr Walks was a fantastic professor and helped me understand the material from a background very different from my own. Also very handsome!

rComments: He's a great prof., passion in what he teaches, sense of humour, very friendly and easy to talk to, term tests and exams were basically comprised of mainly lecture material (short answer and essay questions) and the past exam was very helpful. Loved this class.
Really Nice, very clear and organized, definitely recommend.
bad lecturing style of endless overheads & talking while you're trying to copy. however exams use very little textbook material (primarily lecture material)

I find him quite unhelpful whenever I ask a question, and he even gets a little rude somtimes.  I don't get anything out of the lecture because he is talking while putting pages and pages of long paragraphs to copy down.  I can't listen to him or read what I am writing. Class was interesting. WAY too many detailed overheads to write down so bring a laptop if you own one! Textbook was good. Attend class. You should be capable of receiving a great mark in this course.
